That also changes how I’d think about the “fields.”

Maybe they’re not independent fields at all.

Maybe they’re phases.

Like matter.

Luck isn’t a thing.

It’s one phase of optionality under uncertainty.

Charisma might be trust interacting with attention.

Magic might be ignorance interacting with causality.

Flow might be competence interacting with friction.

Wisdom might be memory interacting with time.

So instead of asking:

“What are the fields?”

Perhaps ask:

“What are the substrates from which all these fields emerge?”

Candidate substrates:

* Attention
* Time
* Energy
* Information
* Memory
* Constraints
* Relationships
* Transformation
* Uncertainty
* Value

Everything else may be different organizations of those.

